📌 Overview
This project showcases an end-to-end E-commerce Sales Analysis Dashboard built using Microsoft Excel.
It involves data cleaning, transformation, analysis, and visualization using advanced Excel functionalities like Pivot Tables, Conditional Formatting, and Lookup Functions.
The dashboard provides actionable insights into sales performance, customer behavior, and regional trends.

🎯 Objective
To analyze raw e-commerce transaction data
To perform data cleaning and preprocessing
To extract meaningful business insights
To build an interactive and visually appealing dashboard

🛠️ Tools & Techniques Used
Microsoft Excel
Pivot Tables & Pivot Charts
IF Function
VLOOKUP / XLOOKUP
Sorting & Filtering
Conditional Formatting
Data Cleaning Techniques

🔧 Data Processing & Analysis Steps
📊 Data Transformation:
Calculated Total Revenue (Quantity × Price)
Computed Average Order Value
Handled missing discount values
Removed duplicate Order_ID records
Split Customer_Name using Text to Columns

🔍 Data Analysis:
Counted number of orders by Region
Classified orders as 'High Value' (Price > 2000) using IF function
Sorted data by Price (Highest to Lowest)
Filtered Cancelled Orders

🎨 Data Enhancement:
Applied Conditional Formatting to highlight Discount > 5%
Used VLOOKUP/XLOOKUP to fetch product details

📊 Pivot Tables Created
📌 Sales by Category
📌 Sales by Region & Payment Mode

📈 Dashboard Features
📊 Total Sales Overview
🧾 Total Orders Count
🏆 Top Performing Category
🌍 Region-wise Sales Analysis
📉 Interactive charts (Bar, Line, Pie)
🎛️ Dynamic filtering using slicers

📊 Key Insights
Identified top-performing product categories
Analyzed regional sales distribution
Evaluated high-value customer orders
Observed impact of discounts on sales
Tracked cancelled orders and patterns

